    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-12-15T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-12-15T18:00:00-05:00" n="701"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d701">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/5721: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Nanking (<persName type="to">Peck</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-12-15T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 15, 1932—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>75. For the Minister. Your December 13, 1 p.m., reference and last paragraph.</p>
                <p>1. Department requests that you review carefully the whole text of its mail
                    instruction 853,<note n="82" xml:id="d701fn82">August 26, 1932, <ref
                            target="#pg_621">p. 621</ref>.</note> especially the last paragraph.</p>
                <p>Department feels that when next this subject is broached to the Chinese
                    Government the approach should be made in a manner which will carry conviction
                    that this Government regards the matter seriously. Department therefore does not
                    approve of “sounding out” the Minister for Foreign Affairs at this time.</p>
                <p>2. Department requests your comment at an early date, by cable or naval radio,
                        (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) on the contemplated line of procedure outlined in
                    its No. 853 and (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) whether in your opinion the near
                    future would be a propitious moment to make strong representations in this
                    connection.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_SHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
